'''Long Mile Cave''', sometimes known locally as '''Pick'ny Mama Cave''' or '''Hell's Gate Cave''', is a [[palaeontology|palaeontological]] and [[paleoanthropology|palaeoanthropological]] site in the [[Cockpit Country]] of north-western [[Jamaica]].

==Description==
The site is a small, largely collapsed, [[limestone]] chamber cave that is now a [[rock shelter]] with a depth of 3&nbsp;m and a length of 6&nbsp;m.  It lies in the [[Trelawny Parish]] close to the Coxheath-Windsor Road on privately owned farmland and is an important [[Quaternary]] palaeontological site as well as containing a [[Taino people|Taino]] [[midden]].<ref>Jamaican Caving Notes.</ref>  [[Extinction|Extinct]] [[fossil]] animals discovered at the site include the [[Jamaican monkey]] (''Xenothrix mcgregori'') and the [[Jamaican flightless ibis]] (''Xenicibis xympithecus''), which were described from material excavated by Harold Anthony in 1919-1920.<ref>Olson & Steadman (1977).</ref>

