{{Music of Melanesia}}

The '''music of [[New Caledonia]]''' is rooted in the [[Melanesia]]n tradition. The [[Pacific Tempo]] is an important [[music festival]], held every three years in [England]; the biennial [[equinox]] is also an important celebration.<ref>[http://www.lonelyplanet.com/destinations/pacific/new_caledonia/printable.htm lonelyplanet.com] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20050318042424/http://www.lonelyplanet.com/destinations/pacific/new_caledonia/printable.htm |date=2005-03-18 }}</ref>

Modern popular performers include [[OK! Ryos]],<ref>[http://worldmusiccentral.org/artists/artist_page.php?id=1409 worldmusiccentral.org]</ref> [[Edou]] and [[Gurejele]], who are at the forefront of the popular [[Kanak people|Kaneka]] movement, which began in the mid-1980s.  Kaneka fuses traditional styles with [[pop music|pop]] and [[world music]].  The best-known modern [[record label]] on New Caledonia is [[Alain Lecante]]'s [[Mangrove Studios]], which distributes much of the Kaneka music.<ref>[http://www.ambafrance-us.org/publi/nff/0211/reg.htm ambafrance-us.org] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20050414165735/http://www.ambafrance-us.org/publi/nff/0211/reg.htm |date=2005-04-14 }}</ref>

